# Trivy ignore file for the kube-coder devlaptop image scan (CI security-scan job).
#
# Only FALSE POSITIVES belong here. Genuinely no-fix findings are dropped by
# `ignore-unfixed: true` in .github/workflows/ci.yml; actionable findings are
# tracked as GitHub issues and must NOT be silenced here.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# code-server bundled-VS-Code version misparse (issue #71)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Trivy reads the bundled VS Code version (1.123.0) from
#   usr/lib/code-server/lib/vscode/package.json
# and matches it against *code-server* advisories. We pin code-server 4.123.0
# (devlaptop/Dockerfile), which is newer than every fix below (3.12.0 / 4.10.1
# / 4.99.4) — so these are false positives. The bundled npm/shell-quote copies
# live inside upstream code-server's VS Code and are not independently
# patchable; they are resolved by bumping the pinned code-server version, at
# which point Trivy re-evaluates them.
CVE-2021-3810
CVE-2023-26114
CVE-2025-47269
CVE-2019-16775
CVE-2019-16776
CVE-2019-16777
CVE-2018-7408
CVE-2026-9277

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Docker CLI binaries — daemon-side CVEs, not applicable + no upstream fix (issue #70)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These are embedded in the client-only Docker binaries this image ships
# (docker-buildx, docker-compose plugin, standalone docker-compose). This image
# has NO docker/containerd daemon — Docker runs in a separate DinD sidecar
# (see CLAUDE.md), so the daemon-side code paths are unreachable here:
#   CVE-2026-34040  github.com/docker/docker  Moby DAEMON authorization bypass
#   CVE-2026-46680  containerd/v2             containerd DAEMON runAsNonRoot bypass
#   CVE-2026-42504  stdlib (Go)               MIME-header decode DoS (not parsed by compose/buildx)
# They are also not fixable today: verified that the latest upstream releases
# (compose v5.1.4, buildx v0.34.1) are still built with Go 1.26.3 and embed
# docker/docker v28.5.2 + containerd v2.2.3 — i.e. no published binary carries
# the fixes yet.
# REVISIT and remove these lines once upstream ships binaries built with
# Go >= 1.26.4 and embedding docker/docker >= 29.3.1 / containerd >= 2.2.4,
# then bump the pinned versions in devlaptop/Dockerfile so Trivy re-validates.
CVE-2026-34040
CVE-2026-46680
CVE-2026-42504

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# More Docker/gh client-binary Go-module CVEs — medium, same class as #70 (issue #76)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Embedded in the same client-only binaries (docker-buildx, docker-compose
# plugin + standalone) and in usr/bin/gh. Verified the latest upstream releases
# (compose v5.1.4, buildx v0.34.1) still embed these — no published binary
# carries the fixes, and the vulnerable code paths (Moby daemon, in-toto
# verification, OTLP exporter, x509 hostname check) aren't reachable from the
# CLI usage in this image. Revisit alongside the #70 entries above when upstream
# ships rebuilt binaries.
CVE-2026-33997          # github.com/docker/docker — Moby daemon privilege issue
CVE-2026-27145          # Go stdlib — x509 VerifyHostname
CVE-2026-42507          # Go stdlib
CVE-2026-39882          # go.opentelemetry.io/otel OTLP exporter
GHSA-pmwq-pjrm-6p5r     # in-toto-golang negation handling (docker-buildx + gh)

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# code-server bundle — more false positives / ancient vendored deps (issue #76)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Same root cause as the code-server block above: Trivy reads the bundled VS
# Code version (1.123.0) for the code-server advisory, and the `npm 1.0.1`
# copies are decade-old deps vendored inside code-server's VS Code, not
# independently patchable. We pin code-server 4.123.0.
CVE-2021-42648          # code-server (VS Code version misparse)
CVE-2013-4116           # npm (bundled in code-server VS Code)
CVE-2016-3956           # npm (bundled in code-server VS Code)
CVE-2020-15095          # npm (bundled in code-server VS Code)
